headline.main: BETTY HICKS CARDS 72; Coast Golfer Leads by Stroke in Wolverine Open Event

docs.snippet: DETROIT, May 30 (AP) -- Fay Crocker of Montevideo, Uruguay, broke par for the fourth straight round today to capture the Wolverine women's open golf tournament.
docs.lead_paragraph: DETROIT, May 30 (AP) -- Fay Crocker of Montevideo, Uruguay, broke par for the fourth straight round today to capture the Wolverine women's open golf tournament.

docs.lead_paragraph: British sterling moved irregularly last week. At the outset it was buoyed by the favorable influence of the Conservatives' victory at the polls on the preceding Thursday and got up to $2.79 17/32, a gain of 3/32 cent over the long holiday (Friday to Tuesday).

headline.main: FOREIGN EXCHANGE RATES Week Ended June 3, 1955
LOUISE SUGGS TAKES EASTERN LINKS TITLE

docs.snippet: The Inter-American Press Association voted at its annual General Assembly in Rio de Janeiro last October to celebrate June 7 as "Freedom of the Press Day." It was recommended that publishers in each country hold some appropriate ceremony on that day...
docs.lead_paragraph: The Inter-American Press Association voted at its annual General Assembly in Rio de Janeiro last October to celebrate June 7 as "Freedom of the Press Day." It was recommended that publishers in each country hold some appropriate ceremony on that day -- presuming they are free to do so.
docs.abstract: ed on Press Freedom Day suggested by Inter-Amer Press Assn; revs situation in Latin Amer

docs.snippet: GENEVA, June 7 -- Six more countries signed tariff agreements with Japan here today. They are Denmark, Finland, Italy, Peru, Sweden and Uruguay. Canada signed yesterday and the United States will sign tomorrow.
